nodes.bodyText:
So this one proposes the changes to bootstrap https://docs.google.com/document/d/1k9nnfZXCyuvWi3MsLSStPMGAyf-UEw2Mvso0ZxDTAG4/edit?ts=5f244687# - which says

A new field will be added to the bootstrap file which will contain a map of CertificateProvider plugin instances (a plugin instance is a unique instantiation of a CertificateProvider with a specific configuration). The key to this map will be an opaque name (agreed upon by the client and the control plane) and the value will be the CertificateProvider name and configuration.

So the new field is "certificate_providers" and the value (JSON object) represents a map of Certificate-provider instance names to (plugin-name + configs) tuple. e.g.
{
    "gcp_id": {
        "plugin_name": "meshca",
        "config": { ...MeshCA config... }
    },
    "local_file": {
        "plugin_name": "file_watcher",
        "config": { ...FileWatcher config... }
    }
}

I will update this PR to represent this structure. Thanks

