In the following example:
"gcp_id": {
        "plugin_name": 123,
        "config": { ...MeshCA config... }
    }

You'll get a ClassCastException from JsonUtil.getString(valueMap, "plugin_name") and that's a RuntimeException and not an IOException. Do you think that one needs to be addressed as well? parseConfig is full of such cases and they will all need to be fixed (or have a common catch clause at the end to create a wrapper IOException around ClassCastException).

